cs.DM, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with problems related to permutations and groups induced by graphs.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the motion of robots (pebbles) on a graph and planning their paths.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes algorithms for solving the problem of pebble motion on graphs with rotations.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with problems related to graphs and their geometric properties.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and proposes algorithms with polynomial time complexity.
